  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nFutures pointing to a mixed open with NASDAQ leading the charge at +1.91% while DOW struggles in negative territory. VIX holding elevated at 29.79 signals underlying tension as Iran war jitters persist, but tech optimism ahead of Mag-7 earnings is driving selective buying.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dallas Fed Manufacturing Index (2:30 PM EST)</strong> - Key regional data with potential market-moving impact amid geopolitical uncertainty</li>\n<li><strong>Treasury Auctions</strong> - Heavy schedule with 2-year and 5-year note auctions testing demand for duration risk</li>\n<li><strong>Mag-7 Earnings Setup</strong> - Tech sector positioning ahead of this week's heavyweight earnings reports</li>\n<li><strong>Oil Price Action</strong> - Iran war premium keeping energy markets volatile, watch for spillover effects</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nClear flight to tech with XLK up 2.81% as traders position for earnings optimism, while defensive sectors get hammered. Healthcare leading the decline at -1.41% with Communication Services also weak at -1.58%. Risk-on rotation playing out despite elevated VIX, suggesting selective optimism over broad fear.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Tech momentum building into Mag-7 earnings week with NASDAQ futures showing strong pre-market conviction. Sector rotation suggests confidence in growth names despite macro headwinds.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Iran war escalation driving dual narrative - oil price inflation concerns versus potential tech safe-haven flows. Market choosing growth over value today.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>VIX above 29 with mixed index performance screams internal weakness. DOW red while NASDAQ rips suggests narrow leadership that could reverse quickly on any earnings disappointments.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY $710</strong> - Pre-market support, break below targets $705 gap fill</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ $670</strong> - Resistance zone, clear break opens $680 target</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 32</strong> - Critical resistance, break above signals fear escalation</li>\n<li><strong>XLK $240</strong> - Tech sector breakout level, failure here kills the momentum trade</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
